  <eligibility>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Variceal bleeding secondary to cirrhosis and portal hypertension

          -  Child's Class A or B cirrhosis of any etiology

          -  Patients who have failed endoscopic therapy (sclerotherapy or banding) of varices; or
             patients who are not candidates for endoscopic therapy

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Prior shunt procedure

          -  Portal vein thrombosis

          -  Polycystic liver disease

          -  Intractable ascites

          -  Prior organ transplant

          -  Any medical intractable disease
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
    <gender>All</gender>
